column5: Heading up to the cottage in wasaga tomorrow to spend 4 days on the notty, it normally gets a earlier run and with the cooler temps and all the rain last week i figure there should be a bunch of fish in the river.  Such a wonderful time of the year!
I may pop over there this weekend as well to try this river fishing!
Good luck to you both. Don't forget to bring the click click magic box with you.
Incredible, make sure to report with pics, 4 days of steelheading sounds like heaven.
Just got a new water proof digital camera...now just need something to take pics of...
Weather isn't going to be on your side this weekend.  80 degrees on Sat with sun.  Better get there early!
